          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Firstly let me introduce me. I am NRI who wish to return back to homeland. So I was looking for school nearby my location and I found this school as one of the good school. So I enquired about the admission. They are admission process wasn’t transparent they initially told us there will be interaction with parents and we also shared the current countries school report. They asked for parent interaction and later ask kids to join that interaction and started interviewing them without any prior notice. However my younger child was able to answer all of their interview questions but my elder one was struggling. I am fine if they have not given a position for elder one but after a long wait after 2 months we were inform that both of them do not qualify. I am fine this answer however the agony they made to my younger child who was happy by answering all their question had now depressed. Also they haven’t provide valid reason for their disqualification of my kids. When asked it was mentioned it’s taken on principal . So I wanted to know what is discrimination do that principal shown to my kids ?? What is process they follow for NRI candidates . If they are not will they should have if informed in 1st connect itself . I am feeling it as scam on NRI who are looking for admission. Lots of discrimination shown . I will try to investigate on it further once we are back on home land. Else it is a biggest scam on application of NRI candidates to this SRM school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
